WHEREAS, though initially intended to be temporary, Dr. Savoie's remarkable
leadership, strategic vision, and unwavering commitment to educational excellence quickly
earned the confidence and admiration of state leaders, prompting the Board of Regents to
appoint him permanently to the state's highest postsecondary education office; and
WHEREAS, Dr. Savoie served with extraordinary distinction as Louisiana
commissioner of higher education for twelve years under three gubernatorial
administrations, where he became widely respected as a consensus builder, reformer, and
champion for students and institutions across the state; and
WHEREAS, during his tenure as commissioner, Dr. Savoie played an instrumental
role in reshaping and modernizing Louisiana's higher education landscape through
transformative reforms, including restructuring higher education governance, creating the
Louisiana Community and Technical College System, strengthening teacher education
programs, securing full funding for the higher education formula, championing student
retention and completion in the wake of hurricanes Katrina and Rita, and establishing
Louisiana's first statewide needs-based financial aid program, thereby expanding educational
access and opportunity for countless students and families; and
WHEREAS, former Governor Kathleen Babineaux Blanco aptly described Dr.
Savoie as "the commissioner who has had the most positive influence on all of education in
Louisiana," reflecting the profound and lasting impact of his leadership upon the state's
educational system; and
WHEREAS, in 2008, following the retirement announcement of longtime UL
Lafayette President Dr. Ray P. Authement, Dr. Savoie sought the opportunity to return to his
alma mater and continue its legacy of excellence, bringing with him unmatched statewide
experience, national perspective, and a deep and abiding love for UL Lafayette; and
WHEREAS, the University of Louisiana System Board of Supervisors selected Dr.
Savoie to serve as UL Lafayette's sixth president, and on July 2, 2008, he began a historic
tenure defined by innovation, strategic growth, academic excellence, and transformational
achievement; and
WHEREAS, under Dr. Savoie's visionary leadership, UL Lafayette experienced
unprecedented advancement and emerged as one of the nation's premier public research
