universities, earning the prestigious Carnegie R1 classification and placing UL Lafayette
among the top tier of research institutions in the United States; and
WHEREAS, during his presidency, Dr. Savoie led transformative investments in
research and development, resulting in research expenditures increasing by nearly two
hundred percent between 2014 and 2021, while also overseeing significant campus
expansion and modernization through the construction of new academic buildings, residence
halls, research laboratories, athletic and student-centered facilities, as well as the acquisition
and development of UL Lafayette's Health Sciences Campus; and
WHEREAS, Dr. Savoie championed academic innovation and workforce
development through the expansion of undergraduate and graduate degree programs
designed to meet the evolving needs of Louisiana's economy and global society, while also
fostering stronger partnerships between UL Lafayette and the surrounding community; and
WHEREAS, in the years following 2020, UL Lafayette achieved record enrollment
in undergraduate and graduate programs, reflecting the growing national reputation of the
institution and the success of Dr. Savoie's steadfast commitment to student achievement,
academic excellence, and institutional advancement; and
WHEREAS, Dr. Savoie devoted thirty-five years of service to the University of
Louisiana at Lafayette, including seventeen transformative years as president, and in
recognition of his extraordinary leadership, enduring contributions, and unwavering
dedication to the institution, the University of Louisiana System Board of Supervisors
conferred upon him the title of president emeritus upon his retirement; and
WHEREAS, throughout his distinguished career, Dr. E. Joseph Savoie has
exemplified integrity, humility, wisdom, and servant leadership, leaving an indelible mark
upon higher education in Louisiana and inspiring generations of students, educators,
administrators, and public servants through his tireless dedication and extraordinary
accomplishments; and
WHEREAS, Dr. Savoie's legacy will endure not only through the institutions he
strengthened and the reforms he championed, but also through the countless lives he
influenced and the enduring belief that education remains one of the most powerful forces
for opportunity, progress, and public good.
